 for open interpritation on what the strenght of a particular mage might be!  In today's game a warrior is just a meat shield for most of his life.  A warrior is only as good as his strength and his weapon.  But what if a warrior could be more?  An open architecture could allow a warrior to have abilities that EQ simply can not do with out class balance issues.   </P><P>I happen consider the father of fantasy to be Tolken.  Yet in his middle earth (verrants claim of the vision is a very similar middle earth view) Gandalph weilded a sword.   A battle mage.  EQ2 could allow for that.... at a price.  I want to see more about what the game allows for and what its restrictions are before I decide that the game sucks and its a waste.  As I said earlier... Ive dabbled with DAoC and AO and there are things in the game I did like... most of it I didnt.  If Verrant keeps the positives of EQ and implements the good things about these other games then it could be an incredible game.</P><P></P><P>Ahh... see how death becomes you?</font></td>
