        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> You guys crack me up.</P><P>You're acting like you're supposed to get a paycheck once you get to lvl 60 and beat the game.  And now that they're going to shut it all down, you're not going to get paid.  All that hard work, long hours and exhaustive effort down the drain.  Wait a minute...</P><P>Wasn't this supposed to be fun?  If you're not enjoying yourself while playing EQ, why are you playing?  All this time and effort you've put into EQ doesn't mean <a href="mailto:s@$t">s@$t</a> in the big picture anyway - all it is is a way to distract yourself from real life.  I understand that people get attached to their characters, I'm VERY attached to mine, and it'll be a sad day when Riganzi gets logged off for the last time.  But I get attached to all my chars, and I do it fairly quickly.  One of the allures of this game is that it draws you in so much.  I'm sure EQ2 will be just as easy to get attached to, and when EQ2 gets replaced by whatever follows it, I'll mourn my characters for about 30 seconds while I'm creating my new ones.</P><P>Maybe it's because I've moved between table-top games too many times to get attached to any one character... I get myself attached to the play.  If EQ2 has better play, you bet I'll sign up.</P><P>EQ can't be defeated.  There isn't a final quest that, upon completion, rolls the credits.  There's enough other games out there that will offer closure, EQ doesn't need to be one of them.</P><P>And guys, we've all spoken about all the broken things in this game.  There's too much broken stuff to be able to realistically fix it all.  There's too many constraints in this old clunky code, and it'd take them twice as long to re-code EQ1 as it would to re-write the game and make a new one.  I'm glad that they're doing this, and I'll absolutely give EQ2 a shot.  There will be other games out there, sure, but these guys know EXACTLY where their old codes went wrong, and it gives them an advantage over people who are new to the genre.  I think they're right on in saying what the folks with the sneak-peek at PC Gamer leaked... They've learned a lot about what works and what doesn't.  And they can account for those things much better in a new game that they just start over with.</P><P>This wasn't going to last forever.  Keep your view of EQ in perspective... it is just a way to pass the time.  EQ has the unfortunate combination of being able to pass an extraordinary amount of time and have absolutely NOTHING to show for it in the end.  We all knew that going in.</P><P>From what's been leaked, I doubt it'd be possible, much less feasible, for them to make characters transferrable.  And even if they did, I'd probably start over.  Moving an old char from EQ1 to EQ2 would be almost on the same level as buying a lvl 60 warrior in ToV gear on Ebay.  I want to play the new game from the beginning.</P><P>One thing I would ask is that VI offer some sort of ACCOUNT transfers... it'd be nice if they at least offered a discount to existing EQ1 players to switch to the new game.</P><P>And the other thing we have to remember... this is NEXT OCTOBER.  18 MONTHS.  Yeah, they'll be moving staff around to get to work on it early.  Personally, I don't think we'll see anything new for EQ1 after PoP comes out.  But they're not going to shut everthing down this winter.  They'll support it as long as they can, maybe they won't f00k up like Blizzard did and try to keep fans from taking over the servers and continuing to support online play... (I think that was Blizzard, wasn't it?  I forget...  anyway, you all know what I'm talking about)</P><P>*shrug* maybe I'm way off base.  Maybe I play the game for the wrong reasons... All I know is I'm having fun.  I'm sure they're not going to make EQ2 with the intention of it being work, either.</P><P>Death is your friend.  Introduce everyone you meet.<BR></font></td>
